{\"video_title\":\"Question Refinement Pattern\",\"transcript\":\"‚ÄčA really simple way to improve ‚Äčour interactions with large language model like ‚Äčchat GPT is to use the question refinement pattern. ‚ÄčThis is a really simple idea and hopefully it'll ‚Äčinspire other ideas from you patterns that you could use. ‚ÄčBut basic idea behind this ‚Äčis that we watch chat GPT or another ‚Äčlarge language model whenever we ask ‚Äča question to try to improve our question. ‚ÄčSo the fundamental idea ‚Äčbehind this is that we may not have ‚Äčas much information or underlying thought ‚Äčbehind our question as ‚Äčchat GPT has from it's training data. ‚ÄčSo it may be able to infer patterns and ‚Äčother questions or words or things that are ‚Äčuseful when asking questions on ‚Äčthis particular topic or when trying to ‚Äčrequest something be done on a particular topic. ‚ÄčIf you think about it, ‚Äčthese large language models are ‚Äčtrained on patterns and language. ‚ÄčIf we give it, ‚Äčmaybe a more general question and ask it to refine it, ‚Äčit can use it to knowledge of what other things are ‚Äčasked about in the context ‚Äčof the question we've given it, ‚Äčor what other words are typically ‚Äčassociated with that type of question ‚Äčthat might help improve our question make it more ‚Äčspecific or provide additional context for other things. ‚ÄčSo intuitively what we're trying to do is we're using ‚Äča general question and we're ‚Äčtapping into the large language models, ‚Äčunderstanding of patterns and ‚Äčlanguage around that topic of ‚Äčthat question in order to ‚Äčcreate an improved version of it. ‚ÄčThe pattern behind this is really quite simple, ‚Äčall we need to do is say whenever ‚ÄčI ask a question or you can give it ‚Äčsome scope to this just for the next question or ‚Äčfor the next three questions or whatever you want to do, ‚Äčyou say something like whenever I ask a question, ‚Äčsuggests a better question and ‚Äčask me if I would like to use it instead. ‚ÄčThis is just a really simple idea, ‚Äčwe want to always try to have the best questions, ‚Äčbest prompts to interact with the large language model. ‚ÄčSo we will simply tell it whatever I ‚Äčdo ask or suggest a refinement. ‚ÄčI'm going to show you a little tweak to this, ‚Äčthat's a really helpful tweak to know, ‚Äčwhich is, we can say whenever I ask a question suggests ‚Äča better question and ‚Äčask me if I would like to use it instead. ‚ÄčThis is a nice little refinement that ‚Äčhelpful from a user experience perspective because what ‚Äčwe're doing now is not only are we going to tell ‚Äčthe large language model to create ‚Äčthe question that's better, ‚Äčbut rather than requiring us to go and cut and paste it ‚Äčor tell the large language model ‚Äčuse the question that you just generated, ‚Äčwe just have it say do you ‚Äčwant to use this question instead. ‚ÄčIf we say yes, it uses that question, ‚Äčif we say no, it should use our original question. ‚ÄčSo it's a nice little tweak to ‚Äčthis pattern that can make it even easier to use. ‚ÄčNow every time we ask a question, ‚Äčthe large language model will go and try to improve it. ‚ÄčSo let's look at an example of this. ‚ÄčI'm going to start off with a generic question which is, ‚Äčshould I go to Vanderbilt University? ‚ÄčIf we look at this question we can see it's ‚Äčreally ambiguous and vague, ‚Äčand if somebody was asking you this question, ‚Äčshould I go to Vanderbilt University or as ‚Äča faculty member or somebody was asking me, ‚Äčshould I go to Vanderbilt University? ‚ÄčWhere not only is this a big decision for the person. ‚ÄčBut there's really not ‚Äčenough information at this point ‚Äčfor me to make a decision. ‚ÄčSo a better question is ‚Äčgoing to help give me more information about ‚Äčthe criteria that you're using to decide do ‚Äčthese types of what are the pros and cons, ‚Äčhow do you weigh them and decide if it's the right fit. ‚ÄčThat's exactly what we see chat GPT doing. ‚ÄčChat GPT says sure, ‚Äčhere's a suggested question. ‚ÄčWhat factors should I consider when ‚Äčdeciding whether or not to attend Vanderbilt University, ‚Äčand how do they align with ‚Äčmy personal goals and priorities, ‚Äčand then it says would you ‚Äčlike to use this question instead. ‚ÄčThis is a really nice pattern ‚Äčbecause once we've turned it on ‚Äčwe can begin asking ‚Äčquestions and automatically getting ‚Äčbetter versions of our question. ‚ÄčOne of the things that's ‚Äčnice about this is that also helps ‚Äčus to reflect on what we're asking for, ‚Äčand if we see a question come back like this, ‚Äčwhat factors should I ‚Äčconsider when deciding whether or not to intend at ‚ÄčVanderbilt University and how do they ‚Äčalign with my personal goals and priorities, ‚Äčeither will see that and see that's ‚Äča really useful question and that's how I ‚Äčreally would have phrased it if I'd thought ‚Äčabout it better or more. ‚ÄčBut sometimes what we'll also see is that the path it's ‚Äčtaking this down is not ‚Äčthe one we want to go and we'll realize ‚Äčthere's lots of paths, ‚Äčlots of ways of answering the question ‚Äčand we need to give some additional context. ‚ÄčSo not only is this useful in many cases of getting ‚Äča better question but sometimes it's helpful to us to ‚Äčsee that a question could be ‚Äčinterpreted in many different ways, ‚Äčthere's many different pieces ‚Äčof information that may be needed to make ‚Äčan effective decision and so by seeing one version of ‚Äča refined question will ‚Äčidentify missing pieces of information. ‚ÄčSo for example, if I really ‚Äčcare about computer science at Vanderbilt, I might think, ‚ÄčI should have mentioned that I'm planning on majoring in ‚Äčcomputer science or if the town that I'm ‚Äčgoing to be and when I got ‚Äčto college is really important that I might want to ‚Äčsay something about Nashville and living in Nashville. ‚ÄčWe want to make sure that you think ‚Äčthrough the question really effectively and ‚Äčthis is a pattern that can help us ‚Äčreally put in on producing better questions, ‚Äčlearning from the refinements to ‚Äčthe questions and also using the questions, ‚Äčthe refinements to understand what's missing in ‚Äčthe context that we might want to ‚Äčintroduce in order to get a better output.\"}